  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 14:25-26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". After the meal was over, Jesus goes forward on His journey towards Jerusalem, and draws with Him much people, as they thronged everywhere in Galilee upon the marvellous teacher (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 12:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 9:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and elsewhere). But the nearer He is to His own painful self-surrender, the more decidedly and ideally His claims emerge. To the dependent and undecided people going with Him He addresses Himself with the claim of the perfect, most self-denying surrender required of His disciples. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the same claim, although less ideal in form, is made, and is addressed exclusively to the apostles. With the Christian communions (Weizsäcker) these instructions have even in Luke nothing to do.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἴ τις ἔρχεται πρός με",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] namely, with a view to hearken to me as a confessor and follower.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μισεῖ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "minus amat",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or the like (Kuinoel, de Wette, and many others); see, on the other hand, on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 6:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Father, mother, etc., as even also the special desire for the preservation of one’s own life (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), are assumed as being ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in opposition",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to fellowship with Christ (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 12:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), so that, according to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 6:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 16:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in respect of the love of the one Lord the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "hatred",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of others must find place.[176]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
